“In the updated architecture, the client directly uploaded weekly CSV files into Azure Data Lake Storage Gen2. We implemented event-based ingestion using Azure Event Grid integrated with Azure Data Factory Event Triggers. Whenever a new file arrived in the landing container, the pipeline automatically started and ingested the raw CSV data into the Bronze layer in parquet format. After Bronze ingestion, watermarking and CDC-based incremental processing logic identified newly modified records for downstream Silver transformations. In the Silver layer, we performed cleansing, null handling, flattening, schema enforcement, deduplication, and validation logic. Finally, the Gold layer created business-ready star schema models optimized for PowerBI reporting and analytical consumption.”
In the second stage, we built a metadata-driven pipeline in ADF for Bronze layer ingestion into ADLS Gen2. The pipeline was fully parameterized using dynamic content, allowing the same framework to process multiple tables and feeds without hardcoding logic. We implemented incremental loading using watermarking and CDC (Change Data Capture) techniques, where the pipeline dynamically fetched the latest processed timestamp from a control table and extracted only newly updated records.

The orchestration flow included Lookup activities, Set Variables, Copy Activities, If Conditions, and dynamic sink partitioning based on ingestion date and source system. We also designed the pipeline with idempotent pipeline principles to avoid duplicate processing during reruns.

One practical challenge was that ADF generated empty files when no new records were available. To solve this, we implemented conditional file cleanup logic using If Condition and Delete activities, ensuring that unnecessary empty files were automatically removed before downstream processing.

Overall, this architecture helped us create a scalable, reusable, and optimized ingestion framework with reliable CDC handling, dynamic execution capability, and efficient Bronze layer storage management for downstream Databricks Medallion processing.”



